=== RAW MODEL ANSWER ===
We need to design a synthesis of alizarin yellow R (structure: 2-hydroxy-4-(phenylazo)-benzoic acid? Actually alizarin yellow R is 2-hydroxy-4-(4-nitrophenylazo)benzoic acid? Wait given SMILES: O=C(O)c2cc(N=Nc1ccc(N(=O)=O)cc1)ccc2O. That is salicylic acid (2-hydroxybenzoic acid) with azo coupling at position 4 (para to OH) to a nitroaniline derived azo group: N=N attached to a nitro-substituted phenyl (para-nitro). The azo partner is p-nitroaniline (4-nitroaniline). So the target is salicylic acid (2-hydroxybenzoic acid) coupled via azo to p-nitroaniline.

We need to start from aniline (unsubstituted) and salicylic acid, plus any other reagents. So we need to convert aniline to p-nitroaniline (by nitration) then diazotize to form diazonium salt, then couple with salicylic acid

